<br>
  I see no reason a Dark Elf, any class, would consort with a gnome, of any class. There are lines to be drawn. There may be other evil race/class combinations, but does that mean that they should be in?<br>
<br>
  Point: If there were such a thing as halfling necromancers, would we allow them into our guild? I should hope not, Dark Elves HATE halflings, with a vengeance. Do you see what I'm getting at? Just because a race/class can be evil, doesn't necessarily mean they fit our "style". <br>
<br>
  Trolls, Ogres, and Dark Elves are the "heart" of our guild, seeing as they are the major evil races. Iksar are more evil than the DEs. Gnomes, as a RACE, are GOOD, hence should not be allowed. Humans as a race are NEUTRAL, which allows them a loop-hole. As for Erudites, I assume NEUTRAL as well.<br>
<br>
  I am probably sounding a little "prejudiced", but shouldn't I be? Shouldn't WE be? Very clear, very strict lines should be made. This is how I think they should be drawn:<br>
<br>
  ALLOWED<br>
ALL Dark Elves<br>
ALL Trolls<br>
ALL Ogres<br>
ALL Iksar<br>
Human SKs and Necros worshipping either Bertox or Inny<br>
Erudite SKs and Necros worshipping either Bertox or Inny  <br>
<br>
  NOT ALLOWED<br>
ALL Halflings<br>
ALL Barbarians<br>
ALL Gnomes<br>
ALL Dwarves<br>
ALL Half-Elves<br>
ALL High-Elves<br>
ALL Wood-Elves<br>
Any Erudite not of the above<br>
Any Human not of the above<br>
<br>
  I realize this limits our variety in the Guild, but isn't that what we're about? Separating US from THEM? The EVIL from the GOOD? If I were to be extremely puritan about it all, I'd say no Humans or Erudites whatsoever, but I realize how valuable an ally they can be, and also how evil, despite their race.<br>
<br>
  I'm rambling now. <br>
<br>
  Just my 2.5 trillion platinum <p><br>Malekithe
