I have studied Norrathian lore. The Heretics I view as evil. Miragul and his followers bought the study of necromancy from Neriak. And for that they were banished from Erudin and forced to make Paineel their home. They were outcasts for centuries learning the dark arts. Never to walk amongst their persecutors again.<br>
<br>
Humans and Gnomes on the other hand practice their arts in secrecy. As do other races. We need people who are inherantly evil and have no desire to hide or mask it. By choosing to be a necromancer or shadowknight one chooses to step out on evil faith. That's why certain humans and gnomes, and followers of Miragul are tolerated in Neriak.<br>
<br>
We accept erudite and human necros/SKs. We also accept gnomes necromancers. For any others wishing to walk in darkness with us we have a requirement. That is to truly embrace the evil that is inherant in all of us. Let it rule over and shadow any goodness that dwells in you. And this isn't taken at face value. You must turn your back on those who seek to blind the masses with the ignorance of a greater &quot;good.&quot; You must seek them out and expose their idiodacy of peace &amp; tranquility. There is no peace. There is no tranquility. The gods dwell in hatred and war and so shall the mortals. Each potential member must prove their allegiance and intentions to serve evil. This includes those who are evil by nature and not just circumstances. Once this is completed you are welcome to walk among us.<br>
<br>
For those who preach the rhetoric of evil, we challenge them to practice it. If you are a elf or human or other good race and claim to be evil then we present a test. Deny your kin and your home lands. Walk in the wilderness of pain and isolation. Destroy those who are the enemies of our cause and prove your worth. Once you have atoned for any goodness that dwells in you, enter the home of Innoruuk's children in Neriak. The residents recognize true evil and will slay those who haven't fully embraced it. <br>
<br>
